HEADWORD: Inlagation
<hw>In"la*ga"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Law L.
<ets>inlagatio</ets>, fr. <ets>inlagare</ets> to restore to law. See
<er>In</er>, and <er>Law</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Old Eng. Law)</fld> <def>The
restitution of an outlawed person to the protection of the law;
inlawing.</def> <rj><au>Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

